Description: Head and upper body of a calcite statue of a man wearing a short wig with a uraeus; plain back-pillar.
Curator's comments: Published (as 118544) : H. R. Hall, 'A Ramesside Royal Statue from Palestine', JEA 14 (1928), 280 pl. 29.1
Condition: incomplete - head and upper body only
Acquisition notes: Transferred from WAA on 26 May 1961. Still bears their number 118544.
